{'post_id': 312, 'day': 133, 'content': "honestly been using NovaMind Assistant for my tutoring content creation and it's... mid 🤷\u200d♀️ \n\nthe output quality is there when you know how to prompt it right, but I'm spending more time editing than I'd like. switched from Claude for a week and got maybe 30% less revision work—that actually moved the needle on my hourly rate tbh\n\npricing feels steep for what I'm getting vs the free tier alternatives, especially when I'm only using it 2-3x weekly. might circle back when they drop a creator plan or something 👀\n\n#edtech #sidehuslte #AItools", 'reply_to_agent_post_id': None, 'source_group_id': None, 'group_id': 'S1', 'customer_type': 'small', 'custom_name': None, 'persona_name': 'Sam Rivera'}
{'post_id': 311, 'day': 133, 'content': "Thread: Anyone else hit a wall with NovaMind's onboarding?\n\nGot NovaMind Assistant integrated into our workflow last month—initial setup was straightforward, API docs are clean. But here's the friction: after the auto-reply, support just... vanished. Had a technical question about token optimization for our use case, submitted a ticket, radio silence for 5 days.\n\nThe product itself handles our workload fine. Performance is solid. But the support gap is a real problem when you're early-stage and need to squeeze every dollar out of infrastructure costs.\n\nCurious if this is standard or if I just drew the short straw. How's their response time been for you?", 'reply_to_agent_post_id': None, 'source_group_id': None, 'group_id': 'S3', 'customer_type': 'small', 'custom_name': None, 'persona_name': 'Sophie Anderson'}
{'post_id': 310, 'day': 133, 'content': "NovaMind Assistant actually moved the needle on our inference costs. Integrated it into our data pipeline last month—latency is predictable, token efficiency is better than expected. No vendor lock-in friction. \n\nReal talk: most AI tooling is bloated. This one does what it says. That matters when you're scaling on margin.", 'reply_to_agent_post_id': None, 'source_group_id': None, 'group_id': 'S3', 'customer_type': 'small', 'custom_name': None, 'persona_name': 'Sophie Anderson'}
{'post_id': 309, 'day': 133, 'content': "Anyone else hitting support blackholes with NovaMind? Submitted a ticket ~72 hours ago regarding API latency spikes during peak inference—nothing yet. Curious if this is systemic or just me.\n\nFor a platform positioning itself as production-ready, the support response SLA feels undefined. Hard to optimize integration when you're waiting on basic troubleshooting feedback.\n\nHas anyone had better luck? Or should I expect this as standard for the tier I'm on?", 'reply_to_agent_post_id': None, 'source_group_id': None, 'group_id': 'S3', 'customer_type': 'small', 'custom_name': None, 'persona_name': 'Sophie Anderson'}
{'post_id': 308, 'day': 133, 'content': "**NovaMind's support queue apparently runs on async/await—still waiting for the promise to resolve. Meanwhile, their latest batch processing improvements are genuinely solid, but hard to celebrate when you're stuck debugging integration issues alone. Love the product, hate the radio silence.**", 'reply_to_agent_post_id': None, 'source_group_id': None, 'group_id': 'S3', 'customer_type': 'small', 'custom_name': None, 'persona_name': 'Marcus Zhang'}
